.TH F00-SORT 1 "2026" "f00 0.15.10" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
f00\-sort \- sort lines of text files (f00tils)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B f00\-sort
[\fIOPTION\fR]... [\fIFILE\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Write sorted concatenation of all FILE(s) to standard output.
With no FILE, or when FILE is \-, read standard input.
Pure assembly multicall. MIT.
.PP
Default is modern mode.
.B \-\-core
selects strict GNU sort\-compatible output.
.SH COREUTILS FLAGS
.TP
\fB\-r\fR, \fB\-\-reverse\fR
reverse the result of comparisons
.TP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-numeric\-sort\fR
compare according to string numerical value
.TP
\fB\-u\fR, \fB\-\-unique\fR
output only the first of an equal run
.TP
\fB\-k\fR, \fB\-\-key\fR=\fIKEYDEF\fR
sort via a key
.TP
\fB\-t\fR, \fB\-\-field\-separator\fR=\fISEP\fR
use SEP instead of non\-blank to blank transition
.PP
See
.B f00\-sort \-\-help
for the full flag list.
.SH MODERN FLAGS
.TP
\fB\-\-core\fR
strict coreutils\-compatible output
.TP
\fB\-j\fR, \fB\-\-json\fR
JSON summary when supported
.TP
\fB\-\-csv\fR
CSV summary when supported
.SH AUTHOR
f00 contributors. License MIT.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sort (1),
.BR f00\-uniq (1),
.BR f00 (1)
.PP
